Interpretive Theory of Culture&rdquo;, in his <em>The Interpretation
of Cultures: Selected Essays</em>, New York: Basic Books, pp.
3&ndash;30.</li>

<li>Gibbard, Allan, 1992, &ldquo;Thick Concepts and Warrant for
Feelings&rdquo;, <em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society</em>,
supplementary volume 66: 267&ndash;83.</li>

<li>Grice, H.P., 1975, &ldquo;Logic and Conversation&rdquo;, in Grice
1989: 22&ndash;40.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1978, &ldquo;Further Notes on Logic and
Conversation&rdquo;, in Grice 1989: 41&ndash;57.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1989, <em>Studies in the Way of Words</em>,
Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Harcourt, Edward and Alan Thomas, 2013, &ldquo;Thick Concepts,
Analysis, and Reductionism&rdquo;, in Kirchin 2013b: 20&ndash;43.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199672349.003.0002</li>

<li>Hare, R.M., 1952, <em>The Language of Morals</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1963, <em>Freedom and Reason</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1981, <em>Moral Thinking</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Hay, Ryan J., 2013, &ldquo;Hybrid Expressivism and the Analogy
between Pejoratives and Moral Language&rdquo;, <em>European Journal of
Philosophy</em>, 21(3): 450&ndash;74.
doi:10.1111/j.1468-0378.2011.00455.x</li>

<li>Hess, Leopold, 2021, &ldquo;Slurs: Semantic and Pragmatic Theories
of Meaning&rdquo;, in P. Stalmaszczyk (ed.), <em>The Cambridge
Handbook of the Philosophy of Language</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press, pp. 450&ndash;66. </li>

<li>Heuer, Ulrike, 2012, &ldquo;Thick Concepts and Internal
Reasons&rdquo;, in Ulrike Heuer and Gerald Lang (eds.), <em>Luck,
Value and Commitment: Themes from the Ethics of Bernard Williams</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp. 219&ndash;46.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199599325.003.0009</li>

<li>Hom, Christopher, 2008, &ldquo;The Semantics of Racial
Epithets&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Philosophy</em>, 105(8):
416&ndash;40.</li>

<li>Hume, David, 1739&ndash;40, <em>A Treatise of Human Nature</em>,
David Fate Noron and Mary J. Norton (eds.), Oxford: Oxford University
Press, 2001.</li>

<li>Hurley, S.L., 1989, <em>Natural Reasons</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>Hursthouse, Rosalind, 1996, &ldquo;Normative Virtue Ethics&rdquo;,
in Roger Crisp (ed.), <em>How Should One Live? Essays on the
Virtues</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp. 19&ndash;36.
doi:10.1093/0198752342.003.0002</li>

<li>Jackson, Frank C., 1998, <em>From Metaphysics to Ethics</em>,
Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Kirchin, Simon, 2010, &ldquo;The Shapelessness Hypothesis&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophers&rsquo; Imprint</em>, 10(4) February,
 <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/2027/spo.3521354.0010.004" target="other">available online</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013a, &ldquo;Thick Concepts and Thick
Descriptions&rdquo;, in Kirchin 2013b: 60&ndash;77.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199672349.003.0004</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 2013b, <em>Thick Concepts</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199672349.001.0001</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, <em>Thick Evaluation</em>, Oxford:
Oxford University Press,
 <a href="https://fdslive.oup.com/www.oup.com/academic/pdf/openaccess/9780198803430.pdf" target="other">available online</a>.</li>
 
<li>Kotzee, Ben and Jeremy Wanderer (eds.), 2008, <em>Epistemology
Through Thick and Thin</em>, a special issue of <em>Philosophical
Papers</em>, 37(3).</li>

<li>Kyle, Brent G., 2013a, &ldquo;How Are Thick Terms
Evaluative?&rdquo;, <em>Philosophers&rsquo; Imprint</em>, 13(1)
January,
 <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/2027/spo.3521354.0013.001" target="other">available online</a>.</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013b, &ldquo;Knowledge as a Thick Concept:
Explaining Why the Gettier Problem Arises&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical
Studies</em>, 165: 1&ndash;27. doi:10.1007/s11098-012-9919-2</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;The Expansion View of Thick
Concepts&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 54(4): 914&ndash;44.
doi:10.1111/nous.12289</li>

<li>Lang, Gerald, 2001, &ldquo;The Rule-Following Considerations and
Metaethics: Some False Moves&rdquo;, <em>European Journal of
Philosophy</em>, 9(2): 190&ndash;209. doi:10.1111/1468-0378.00135</li>

<li>Liao, Shen-Yi, Aaron Meskin, and Joshua Knobe, 2020, &ldquo;Dual
Character Art Concepts&rdquo;, <em>Pacific Philosophical
Quarterly</em> 101(1): 102&ndash;128. doi:10.1111/papq.12301</li>

<li>Little, Margaret Olivia, 2000, &ldquo;Moral Generalities
Revisited&rdquo;, in B. Hooker and M.O. Little (eds.), <em>Moral
Particularism</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp.
276&ndash;304.</li>

<li>MacIntyre, Alasdair, 1984, <em>After Virtue</em>, 2<sup>nd</sup>
edition, Notre Dame, IN: University of Notre Dame Press.</li>

<li>McDowell, John, 1981 [1998], &ldquo;Non-Cognitivism and
Rule-Following&rdquo;, in Steven H. Holtzman and Christopher M. Leich
(eds.), <em>Wittgenstein: To Follow A Rule</em>, London: Routledge,
pp. 141&ndash;162. Reprinted in his <em>Mind, Value, and Reality</em>,
Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press (1998), pp.
198&ndash;219.</li>

<li>Miller, Alexander, 2003, <em>Introduction to Contemporary
Metaethics</em>, Cambridge: Polity Press.</li>

<li>M&ouml;ller, Niklas, 2012, &ldquo;The Concepts of Risk and
Safety&rdquo;, in Sabine Roeser, Rafaela Hillerbrand, Per Sandin, and
Martin Peterson (eds.), <em>The Handbook of Risk Theory: Epistemology,
Decision Theory, Ethics, and Social Implications of Risk</em>,
Dordrecht: Springer, pp. 55&ndash;85.
doi:10.1007/978-94-007-1433-5_3</li>

<li>Moore, A.W., 2003, &ldquo;Williams on Ethics, Knowledge, and
Reflection&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy</em>, 78(3):
337&ndash;54. doi:10.1017/S0031819103000330</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Maxims and Thick Ethical
Concepts&rdquo;, <em>Ratio</em>, 19(2): 129&ndash;47.
doi:10.1111/j.1467-9329.2006.00315.x</li>

<li>Murdoch, Iris, 1970, <em>The Sovereignty of Good</em>, London:
Routledge.</li>

<li>Nunberg, Geoff, 2018, &ldquo;The Social Life of Slurs&rdquo;, in
D. Fogal, D. Harris, and M. Moss (eds.), <em>New Work on Speech
Acts</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp. 237&ndash;95.
doi:10.1093/oso/9780198738831.003.0010</li>

<li>Prior, A.N., 1960, &ldquo;The Autonomy of Ethics&rdquo;,
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 38(3):
199&ndash;206.</li>

<li>Putnam, Hilary, 2002, <em>The Collapse of the Fact/Value Dichotomy
and Other Essays</em>, Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Quinn, Warren, 1987, &ldquo;Reflection and the Loss of Moral
Knowledge: Williams on Objectivity&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy &amp; Public
Affairs</em>, 16(2): 195&ndash;209.</li>

<li>Reuter, Kevin, 2019, &ldquo;Dual Character Concepts&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophy Compass</em>, 14(1): e12557.
doi:10.1111/phc3.12557</li>

<li>Reuter, Kevin, Lucien Baumgartner, and Pascale Willemsen, 2024,
&ldquo;Tracing Thick and Thin Concepts Through Corpora&rdquo;,
<em>Language and Cognition</em>, 16(2): 263&ndash;82.
doi:10.1017/langcog.2023.35</li>

<li>Richard, Mark, 2008, <em>When Truth Gives Out</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>Roberts, Debbie, 2011, &ldquo;Shapelessness and the Thick&rdquo;,
<em>Ethics</em>, 121(3): 489&ndash;520. doi:10.1086/658898</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013a, &ldquo;Thick Concepts&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophy Compass</em>, 8(8): 677&ndash;88.
doi:10.1111/phc3.12055</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013b, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s Evaluation, Only
Thicker&rdquo;, in Kirchin 2013b: 78&ndash;98.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199672349.003.0005</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;Depending on the Thick&rdquo;,
<em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society</em> (Supplementary
Volume), 91: 197&ndash;220. doi:10.1093/arisup/akx006</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018a, &ldquo;Thick Epistemic
Concepts&rdquo;, in Conor McHugh, Jonathan Way, and Daniel Whiting
(eds.), <em>Metaepistemology</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press,
pp. 159&ndash;78. doi:10.1093/oso/9780198805366.001.0001</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018b,&ldquo;Why Believe in Normative
Supervenience?&rdquo;, <em>Oxford Studies in Metaethics</em>, 13:
1&ndash;24.</li>

<li>Ryle, Gilbert, 1968, &ldquo;The Thinking of Thoughts: What is
&lsquo;Le Penseur&rsquo; Doing?&rdquo;, in his <em>Collected Papers,
Volume 2</em>, London: Hutchinson, pp. 480&ndash;96.</li>

<li>Rynin, David, 1957, &ldquo;The Autonomy of Morals&rdquo;,
<em>Mind</em>, 66(263): 308&ndash;317.
doi:10.1093/mind/LXVI.263.308</li>

<li>Scanlon, T.M., 2003, &ldquo;Thickness and Theory&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Philosophy</em>, 100(6): 275&ndash;87.</li>

<li>Scheffler, Samuel, 1987, &ldquo;Morality Through Thick and Thin: a
Critical Notice of <em>Ethics and the Limits of Philosophy</em>
[Williams 1985]&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Review</em>, 96(3):
411&ndash;34. doi:10.2307/2185227</li>

<li>Shockley, Kenneth, 2012, &ldquo;Thinning the Thicket: Thick
Evaluative Concepts and Environmental Value&rdquo;, <em>Environmental
Ethics</em>, 34(3): 227&ndash;46.</li>

<li>Sibley, Frank, 2001, <em>Approach to Aesthetics</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon Press.</li>

